- id: oth_pen_001
  category: others
  subcategory: penalties
  difficulty: complex
  question: "A taxpayer fails to furnish a tax invoice for a supply of Rs 10 lakh (tax Rs 1.8 lakh) and the officer finds this during an inspection. The taxpayer claims there was no intent to evade. Determine: (a) applicable penalty provision, (b) quantum, (c) whether Sec 73 or Sec 74 applies, (d) remedy to avoid penalty before SCN."
  expected_sections: ["122(1) CGST Act", "73 CGST Act", "74 CGST Act", "73(5) CGST Act"]
  expected_rules: []
  expected_notifications: []
  expected_conclusion_keywords: ["Section 73", "no fraud", "pay before SCN", "penalty 10% or Rs 10,000", "higher"]
  must_not_say: ["Section 74 always applies"]
  must_cite_verbatim: true
  notes: "Pain-point multi-part: 122(1) general penalty; if no fraud => Sec 73, penalty = 10% of tax or Rs 10,000 whichever higher; payment before SCN under 73(5) = no penalty."

